text: Katreese Barnes (January 3, 1963 – August 3, 2019) was a musician, musical director, and songwriter, best known for being half of the pop duo Juicy with her brother Jerry Barnes, and her work on the music of Saturday Night Live, including the hit "Dick in a Box". She died in 2019 at the age of 56, following a decades-long battle against breast cancer. ==References== Category:1963 births Category:2019 deaths Category:American songwriters Category:Deaths from breast cancer
